cs.MA, cs.RO, cs.SY, cs.AI, cs.CV 

The paper discusses swarm behavior and collision avoidance algorithms, which are commonly studied in the field of multi-agent systems (MAS) and robotics. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.MA (Multiagent Systems). The paper also discusses the use of swarm algorithms on different hardware platforms, which falls under the category of cs.RO (Robotics). The paper proposes a technique to tune the collision avoidance algorithm, which involves optimization and control, falling under the categories of cs.SY (Systems and Control) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper validates its results through simulation, which falls under the category of cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition).
